[h1]Changelog[/h1]

[h2]v0.9.0 — Market Intelligence & Passive Recon (Preview)[/h2]
[list]
[*] Scanner radio passive recon — all 12 vanilla radios enhanced with 4-tier system
[*] Terminal UI overflow guards and text truncation
[*] Exit button on root screens, Back button consistency
[*] Comprehensive loot table expansion (17 → 44 distribution entries)
[*] Critical fix: sendServerCommand SP compatibility
[*] Critical fix: weightFn missing in item selection
[*] Sandbox tooltip %% display fix
[*] PhobosLib 1.38.0 dependency (text truncation utilities)
[/list]

[h2]v0.8.0 — Persistence Migration & VHS Tapes[/h2]
[list]
[*] World-scoped Global ModData persistence (Phase A-E migration)
[*] Server-authoritative economy with daily tick
[*] Passive recon devices: camcorder, field logger, data calculator
[*] VHS-C tapes: 4 quality tiers, crafting, degradation, recycling
[*] VHS tape review at TV CraftBench entity
[*] Intel gathering cooldown (per-location, 12-day default)
[*] 4-state context menu for intel gathering
[*] Dynamic note tooltip showing category-specific items
[*] Append-only event logs for market auditing
[*] 11 item icons generated via gpt-image-1
[*] Client snapshot protocol for multiplayer
[*] Server input validation and admin commands
[/list]

[h2]v0.7.0 — Market Intelligence Engine[/h2]
[list]
[*] Item pool system (5,105 vanilla items mapped to 11 commodity categories)
[*] Price engine with day-to-day drift, reputation-scaled variance, speculation
[*] 18 sub-categories with weighted selection
[*] 13 sandbox options for market weighting and category control
[*] PhobosLib.weightedRandom() and weightedRandomMultiple() utilities
[/list]

[h2]v0.6.0 — Code Quality Audit[/h2]
[list]
[*] POS_Constants.lua centralised (24 cross-file constants)
[*] 35 files refactored — magic numbers and strings extracted
[*] 5 new sandbox options (delivery expiry, scan radii, investment variance)
[*] COLOURS palette delegation to POS_TerminalTheme
[/list]

[h2]v0.5.0 — Screen Stack & Terminal Layout[/h2]
[list]
[*] 3-column terminal layout (NavPanel, ContentPanel, ContextPanel)
[*] Screen stack architecture with API, registry, and guard system
[*] Terminal power consumption (generator fuel drain)
[*] AZAS Frequency Index integration (dual-band registration)
[*] Signal strength system (inverse square law from TransmitRange)
[*] CRT bezel texture and 4 colour themes
[/list]

[h2]v0.4.0 — BBS & Investments[/h2]
[list]
[*] BBS Hub with investments, operations, and courier sections
[*] Investment system with risk/reward simulation
[*] Mission negotiation and cancellation
[*] Pagination support via PhobosLib_Pagination
[*] Street address resolution via Paper Trails
[/list]

[h2]v0.3.0 — Boot Sequence & Resizable Windows[/h2]

[list]
[*] DOS-style boot animation with typewriter character reveal on first terminal open per world-load
[*] Terminal window now resizable via drag handle (compatible with "Resize Any Window" mod)
[*] Click anywhere during boot to skip to operations view
[*] Boot animation speed scales with game speed multiplier
[/list]

[h2]v0.2.0 — Core Gameplay Loop & Terminal UI[/h2]

[list]
[*] Retro CRT-style terminal UI — green monospace text on dark background with scanline effect
[*] Physical setup: right-click any radio near a vanilla desktop computer to connect
[*] "Connect to POSnet" context menu on world-placed and inventory radios
[*] Connection validation: checks radio power, on/off state, and desktop computer proximity
[*] Server-to-client operation delivery via OnServerCommand
[*] 5 built-in starter missions
[*] Welcome guide popup explaining setup and usage
[/list]

[h2]v0.1.0 — Initial Scaffold[/h2]

[list]
[*] POSnet radio channel registration at configurable frequency
[*] Procedural mission generation from registered templates
[*] 5 mission categories
[*] 4 difficulty levels: Easy, Medium, Hard, Critical
[*] Extensible completion detector with item_acquire built-in checker
[*] Player-side operation log with persistence in modData
[*] Server-side timed broadcast system
[*] 6 sandbox options
[*] CI pipeline with 9 automated checks
[/list]
